AI Governance Structure. Four roles with responsibilities: 1) Model Owner (Crown): Model selection, release planning, documentation. 2) Data Steward (Database): Data quality, privacy, bias checks. 3) Ethics Reviewer (Scale): Fairness, transparency, societal impact. 4) Security Owner (Shield): Access control, secrets, attack protection. Gates: Design Review -> Bias/Privacy Review -> Monitoring Gate -> Regular Re-Reviews. Arrows connecting roles to gates. German labels.